  "prompt": "How do you bake frozen hash browns?",
  "response": "Baking frozen hash browns is simple and convenient. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n### Ingredients:\n- Frozen hash browns\n- Cooking oil or non-stick spray (optional)\n- Salt and pepper (to taste)\n- Optional seasonings (such as garlic powder, onion powder, or paprika)\n\n### Instructions:\n\n1. **Preheat the Oven:**\n   - Preheat your oven to 425\u00b0F (220\u00b0C).\n\n2. **Prepare the Baking Sheet:**\n   - Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or lightly grease it with cooking oil or non-stick spray to prevent sticking.\n\n3. **Spread the Hash Browns:**\n   - Spread the frozen hash browns evenly on the baking sheet in a single layer. Do not thaw them beforehand, as they are best cooked from frozen.\n\n4. **Add Oil and Seasoning:**\n   - If desired, drizzle a little oil over the hash browns for extra crispiness. You can also season them with salt, pepper, and any other spices you prefer.\n\n5. **Bake:**\n   - Bake in the preheated oven for about 20-25 minutes. Halfway through the cooking time, use a spatula to flip the hash browns for even cooking.\n\n6. **Check for Doneness:**\n   - Continue baking until they are golden brown and crispy. You can bake them longer if you prefer extra crispiness, but keep an eye on them to prevent burning.\n\n7. **Serve:**\n   - Remove from the oven and let cool slightly before serving. Enjoy them as a side dish or topped with your favorite condiments or ingredients (like cheese, sour cream, or chives).\n\n### Tips:\n- Cooking times may vary based on your oven, so adjust as necessary.\n- For extra flavor, you can mix in some diced onions or bell peppers before baking.\n\nEnjoy your delicious baked hash browns!",
